value.0: Greetings! Welcome to the Lion's Rest. What can I do for you?

Ah, <lad/lass>, you're in the Lion's Rest. This be the line of defence between Amn and Tethyr. Around here there are Shadow Weave Cultists, Orcs, Goblins, and the followers of Loviatar in the Umar Hills. You best watch yourself, you wouldn't want to be captured by any of those with your britches down!

The Amnians are organized out of Fort Ishla and hold the village of Zinner as well as the Castillo de Monte Verde. Most of the front here is their land, and the fort is really meant to guard the pass to keep them from invading. As soon as you cross outside the gate, you're in Amn - so you best keep your wits about you. As far as the war, we're at a bit of a stand-still. The orcs are keeping reinforcements from coming and the Council of Noromath has a deal with the Baroness of Monte Verde. Though, with the Council of Six, who knows when the next attack might be...

The orcs, eh? They're raiding the Ishla Road. I can't say I'm too upset about it, because it keeps the Amnians busy and unable to reinforce. But then, we're mostly at a truce at this point. But who knows, with the Council of Six. As for the orcs themselves, they're living out of some crag in the Umar Hills. I think it might have been a hamlet of some sort at one time.

The Tethyrian Army is under the command of Lord Iybn of the Order of Agis. They're those ones that wear the purple cloaks and hold the Tejarn Gate, eh? Hard looking folk, that's for sure. But you'd have to be coming from Agis. I don't rightly know too much about them, but I hear they're the Queen's undead hunters.

They're the Golden Lion Company, and they're working for the Queen as part of their pennance duty. Most of them are okay, as long as you don't get them too drunk or riled up. But, that's why they all go to the Tejarn Gate to drink instead of somewhere else.
More questions? All right, I've got the mouth if ye've got the ear.
Ah, yes. I can accept your bounties here. Remember, it's right ears only! The ears of goblins, hobgoblins, orcs, ogres or bugbears are good for coin.
Very well. What actions would you like to take?
